      "id": "PopularPost364195",
      "post_content": "Now that we have the ten (and soon fifteen) Gods of Theros, this card became the centerpiece for my WUBRG [Child of Alara](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Child of Alara)/[Progenitus](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Progenitus) EDH deck. You can use [Form of the Dragon](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Form of the Dragon) and [Phyrexian Unlife](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Phyrexian Unlife) to make sure you can't lose, toss out a bunch of Shroud-giving stuff like [Greater Auramancy](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Greater Auramancy) and such, and then lastly grab things such as [Propaganda](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Propaganda) for that last layer of protection. By the way, use [Island Sanctuary](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Island Sanctuary) to stop drawing cards. Once you start grabbing gods, it's all downhill from there. Aside from having a TON of enchantments on the board, if all 15 gods are on the battlefield, they provide enough devotion to animate each other so you can LITERALLY unleash the power of all the Gods at once on your poor victim.",
      "posted_by": "WarioMan",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost364195\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">Now that we have the ten (and soon fifteen) Gods of Theros, this card became the centerpiece for my WUBRG <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Child of Alara\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Child of Alara\">Child of Alara</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Progenitus\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Progenitus\">Progenitus</a> EDH deck. You can use <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Form of the Dragon\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Form of the Dragon\">Form of the Dragon</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Phyrexian Unlife\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Phyrexian Unlife\">Phyrexian Unlife</a> to make sure you can't lose, toss out a bunch of Shroud-giving stuff like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Greater Auramancy\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Greater Auramancy\">Greater Auramancy</a> and such, and then lastly grab things such as <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Propaganda\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Propaganda\">Propaganda</a> for that last layer of protection. By the way, use <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Island Sanctuary\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Island Sanctuary\">Island Sanctuary</a> to stop drawing cards. Once you start grabbing gods, it's all downhill from there. Aside from having a TON of enchantments on the board, if all 15 gods are on the battlefield, they provide enough devotion to animate each other so you can LITERALLY unleash the power of all the Gods at once on your poor victim.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\